extendedInfo.description: Calorie food list alphabeticallyA very helpful app for diet. To lose or gain weight.Its divided by letters, just have to click on the first letter of the food and check the calories.

reviews.title: Legibility
reviews.comment: Can\'t read it, can\'t use it. The colour scheme of faint white lettering reversed out of light blue makes this app almost impossible to read, and there appears no way of changing it. Pity
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Paddy
reviews.comment: Excellent. Just basic food information in 100 gm portions not the silly \"cups\" or \"portions\" of other programs. Includes foods such as spelt and quinoa. Does not try to be clever diet program. Must be European.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Fantastic listing only App
reviews.comment: This, IMHO, is what apps are all about. Elegantly simple, packed with information, and MOST IMPORTANTLY, has NO advertising and does not require any permissions. Have installed on both on my tablet and my phone. My personal thanks to you, Ana :-)
reviews.author: A Sandrs

reviews.title: great list of foods!
reviews.comment: this is great but can you pls tell me if 100g translates to 100ml when it comes to liquids like milk etc? just to be sure...thanks
reviews.author: Maria Frowde

reviews.title: Cool app!
reviews.comment: Simple and easy to use. Love it!
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Did not like
reviews.comment: It didn\'t show how much food was in the amount of calories.
reviews.author: Sara Williams

reviews.title: Impossible to read
reviews.comment: white on pale blue?  Don\'t bother installing this one.
reviews.author: Karen Mason
